Privacy Policy — Unfiltered

Last updated: 2nd December 2025

Unfiltered (“we”, “us”, “our”) is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application (“App”).

1. Information We Collect

a. Information You Provide
	•	Saved favorites or preferences
	•	Optional feedback or support messages

We do not collect sensitive personal data unless you voluntarily provide it.

b. Automatic Data

We may collect anonymized usage data, such as:
	•	Device type
	•	App interactions
	•	Crash logs and diagnostics

This helps us improve app performance and user experience.

2. How We Use Your Information

We use your data to:
	•	Improve and personalize the app
	•	Fix bugs and enhance performance
	•	Provide customer support
	•	Develop new features

We do not sell your data.

3. Third-Party Services

We may use trusted third-party tools (e.g., analytics, crash reporting).
These services follow their own privacy practices and only receive minimal, anonymized information.

4. Your Rights

Depending on your region, you may have rights to:
	•	Access your data
	•	Request deletion
	•	Opt out of analytics

Contact us at arnavsinghal.developer@gmail.com to make a request.

5. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.
The latest version will always be available inside the app and on our website.

6. Contact Us

For questions or concerns, contact us at:
arnavsinghal.developer@gmail.com
